curam.util.message

Class MessageCatalog

  • java.lang.Object
    • curam.util.message.MessageCatalog
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public final class MessageCatalog
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Message catalogs (or more specifically Catalog Entries) are used in the construction of AppExceptions. A message catalog is simply a named object used to identify a group of related application messages. Instances of MessageCatalog are created by generated Curam code, based upon definitions in Curam ".msg" files.
    See Also:
    CatEntry, Serialized Form

      • getCatalog

        public java.util.ResourceBundle getCatalog(java.lang.String localeIn)
        Get the catalog property resource bundle for the passed string locale. If the locale is null, the server default locale bundle be used in the lookup of the catalog. The underlying catalog lookup is provided by JDK class java.util.ResourceBundle. For more information please see the JavaDoc documentation for the appropriate JDK.
        Parameters:
        localeIn - The requested string locale.
        Returns:
        A catalog property resource bundle

      • getCatalog

        public java.util.ResourceBundle getCatalog(java.util.Locale locale)
        Get the catalog property resource bundle for the passed Locale. If the Locale is null, the server default locale bundle will be used in the lookup of the catalog. The underlying catalog lookup is provided by JDK class java.util.ResourceBundle. For more information please see the JavaDoc documentation for the appropriate JDK.
        Parameters:
        locale - The requested locale.
        Returns:
        The catalog property resource bundle
